commentable_entity.ask: Get Johnny Depp back on Fantastic Beasts!
commentable_entity.title: Warner Brothers: Get Johnny Depp back on Fantastic Beasts!
commentable_entity.description:
I believe it’s completely unfair, that over the last year or so Johnny Depp has been a victim to Amber Heard, and to the media. His career has been forever changed due to selfish and jealous actions of his former wife, and former co-star. 

To hear that he has been asked to resign Fantastic Beasts series due to bad media press, and other forms of media is outright disgusting. 

I am a huge supporter of helping men’s mental health, and lowering male suicide as it is at an all time high. With his career ruined and money used to fight the battle against his horrible ex wife, I really hope he can come back with a vengeance with his career.

I am creating this petition to help his cause and get him back his career, please help me and many others support this great actor in getting his fantastic career back.

Thank you

comment:
Johnny Depp is one of the most respected, beloved actors in the world. This is what it took to tear him down to the ground: 
1. The perjury of one PROVEN abuser & liar.
2. A story in a tabloid you wouldn’t use to line a cat box.
3. One corrupt and/or compromised judge. 
Terrifying and shameful, this is spitting in the face of true victims of violence. There are MILLIONS of us worldwide fighting for justice. Amber Heard belongs in prison. Johnny Depp deserves SO MUCH better than this.

comment:
Domestic violence is awful. But in that case the abuser is a woman ! She had a history before Depp, she was obviously manipulative, she cut off his finger, punched him etc...yes the guy was punching cupboards, he also was drinking and using drugs...it is good ?! No it is not ! But that does not mean he is an abuser. Look at the case closer! r
Read the different statements...etc ! Obviously he was victim of a female abuser. 
He lost his libel case against the sun but that does not mean he is a criminal. 
He should not be destroyed for a manipulative and violent woman. 
I am fighting for women's rights, I am standing for feminism. But feminism and women's right does not mean women can abuse men ! I strongly believe there should be no double standards. 
I signed this petition. And if you think it is fair, I invite you to sign.
